Advanced Semiconductor, Alpha, HTC Corp.: Taiwan Stocks Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-08-16T00:22:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/advanced-semiconductor-alpha-htc-corp-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the last close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 182.37 points, or 2.4 percent, to
7,819.39.  Advanced Semiconductor Engineering Inc. (2311)  (2311 TT): The chip
packing and testing company plans to buy back up to 34 million
common shares, or 0.56 percent of total outstanding shares, it
said in a statement to the stock exchange. The company plans to
buy back shares at between NT$20 and NT$45 each from Aug. 16 to
Oct. 15, 2011, it said. The stock rose 4.8 percent to NT$27.25.  Alpha Networks Inc. (3380)  (3380 TT): The networking equipment
maker plans to buy back 15 million common shares, or 3.15
percent of total outstanding stock. The stock gained 7 percent
to NT$21.4.        HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT): Asiaâ€™s second-largest handset producer
by market value reiterated its third-quarter shipment and
revenue forecast at a briefing organized by the Taiwan stock
exchange. Third-quarter revenue will be about NT$137 billion
($4.74 billion), with shipments rising to 13.5 million units,
the Taoyuan, Taiwan-based company said in a statement. The stock
rose 3.4 percent to NT$827.  To contact the reporter on this story:
